@startuml SD16_Account_Deletion
!theme plain
skinparam backgroundColor #FEFEFE
title SD-16: Account Deletion (Anonymity Purge)

actor "User" as U
participant "Astro\nFrontend" as FE
participant "Envoy\nGateway" as GW
participant "Auth\nService" as AUTH
database "pg-auth" as DBAUTH
participant "User\nService" as USER
database "pg-user" as DBUSER
queue "Kafka" as KAFKA
participant "Post\nService" as POST
participant "Comment\nService" as CMT
participant "Vote\nService" as VOTE
participant "Notification\nService" as NOTIF
database "Redis" as REDIS

U -> FE : Click "Delete Account"
FE --> U : Confirmation dialog\n"This cannot be undone"
U -> FE : Confirm + enter password

FE -> GW : POST /api/auth/delete-account\n{password} + JWT
GW -> GW : Validate JWT

== Step 1: Verify Identity ==
GW -> AUTH : gRPC DeleteAccount()
AUTH -> DBAUTH : Fetch credentials
AUTH -> AUTH : Verify password (argon2id)
alt Password incorrect
    AUTH --> GW : 401 Unauthorized
    GW --> FE : JSON {error}
    FE --> U : "Incorrect password"
else Password correct

    == Step 2: Publish Deletion Event ==
    AUTH -> AUTH : Generate deletion_token\n(unique per deletion)
    AUTH ->> KAFKA : Publish "AccountDeleted"\n{user_id, deletion_token}
    AUTH --> GW : 202 Accepted\n"Deletion in progress"
    GW --> FE : JSON {status: "deleting"}
    FE --> U : "Your account is being deleted"

    == Step 3: Async Purge (parallel consumers) ==

    KAFKA ->> POST : Consume "AccountDeleted"
    POST -> POST : UPDATE posts\nSET author = '[deleted]',\nbody = '[deleted]'\nWHERE author_id = user_id

    KAFKA ->> CMT : Consume "AccountDeleted"
    CMT -> CMT : UPDATE comments\nSET author = '[deleted]',\nbody = '[deleted]'\nWHERE author_id = user_id

    KAFKA ->> VOTE : Consume "AccountDeleted"
    VOTE -> VOTE : Anonymize vote records\n(remove user_id, keep scores)

    KAFKA ->> NOTIF : Consume "AccountDeleted"
    NOTIF -> NOTIF : Delete all notifications\nfor user_id
    NOTIF -> NOTIF : Close WebSocket\nif connected

    KAFKA ->> USER : Consume "AccountDeleted"
    USER -> DBUSER : DELETE FROM profiles\nWHERE user_id
    USER -> REDIS : DELETE profile:username\nDELETE karma:user_id\nDELETE communities:user_id

    KAFKA ->> AUTH : Consume "AccountDeleted"\n(self-consume to finalize)
    AUTH -> DBAUTH : DELETE credentials,\nOAuth tokens, email
    AUTH -> REDIS : DELETE OTP, refresh tokens
    AUTH -> DBAUTH : INSERT deletion_log\n(deletion_token, completed_at)
end

note right of DBAUTH
    After purge:
    - No PII remains
    - Posts/comments show [deleted]
    - Vote scores preserved but anonymized
    - Email, password hash, OAuth wiped
end note
@enduml
